    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Route documents with Telegram and MySQL at scale\n\n**Pattern:** Approval Workflow · **Level:** Core · **Trigger:** Form\n\n## What it does\nRoute documents with Telegram and MySQL at scale. It starts from a hosted form submission.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual approvals is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nNew Task Form Submission → Keep Valid Tasks → Route by Work Type → Process 'auto-approve' → MySQL → Merge Routed Work → Stamp Processing Time → Sort Tasks Newest First → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to approval workflow without manual effort\n- Anyone automating approvals in software development\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Responds in seconds\n- Removes copy-paste errors\n- Scales without extra headcount\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: MySQL connection; Slack OAuth2; Telegram bot token.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "dcb76c17-9291-c4d7-4e2e-0d6b1b3372eb",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -290
      ],
      "id": "716490ee-b209-d02d-13a3-633f085752a2",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your approvals process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 4
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
